    "plan_content": "Here is the complete implementation plan. Only **one file** needs to be modified: `src/pipelines.js`. There are exactly **4 surgical edits**:\n\n---\n\n### What I found\n\n- `AutoModelForImageTextToText` already exists in `src/models.js` (line 8736) and supports 11 model families (Florence-2, LLaVA, Qwen2-VL, SmolVLM, PaliGemma, etc.) — but it is **not imported** into `src/pipelines.js` yet and has no pipeline wired up\n- The existing `TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs` typedef (line 215) covers tokenizer + processor + model — exactly what we need, no new typedef required\n- The `SUPPORTED_TASKS` closes at line 3390; the new entry goes right before it\n- The factory JSDoc list is alphabetical; `\"image-text-to-text\"` slots between `\"image-to-text\"` and `\"object-detection\"`\n\n---\n\n### The 4 edits\n\n| # | Where | What |\n|---|-------|------|\n| 1 | Line 41 (import block) | Add `AutoModelForImageTextToText` to the `./models.js` import |\n| 2 | After line 2779 (end of `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline`) | Insert the new typedefs + `ImageTextToTextPipeline` class (~50 lines) |\n| 3 | After line 3389 (end of `image-feature-extraction` in `SUPPORTED_TASKS`) | Add the `\"image-text-to-text\"` task entry |\n| 4 | Line ~3427 (factory JSDoc list) | Add `\"image-text-to-text\"` bullet between `image-to-text` and `object-detection` |\n\n### `_call` design\n\nFollows `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline` closely (single image, image+text → text): processes the image with `this.processor`, tokenizes the text with `this.tokenizer`, passes both `pixel_values` + `input_ids` to `model.generate()`, then decodes with `skip_special_tokens: true`, returning `[{ generated_text: string }]`.",
